DURING AN AERIAL APPLICATION MANEUVER, THE AIRCRAFT DEPARTED 
CONTROLLED FLIGHT AND IMPACTED THE TERRAIN. THE AIRCRAFT WAS 
DESTROYED AND THE PILOT SUSTAINED FATAL INJURIES. SUBSEQUENT 
INVESTIGATION FOUND NOTHING OF A MECHANICAL NATURE IN THE WRECKAGE 
THAT WOULD HAVE CONTRIBUTED TO THE ACCIDENT. 
FAILURE OF THE PILOT-IN-COMMAND TO MAINTAIN CONTROL OF THE AIRCRAFT 
WHILE CONDUCTING AERIAL APPLICATION MANEUVERS IN CLOSE PROXIMITY TO 
THE TERRAIN. 
